modules.description: Handles request routing, response generation, and connection management for Gemini protocol servers. Processes text and binary data streams, and manages HTTP-like status codes and headers. Used to create real-time, protocol-compliant servers for content delivery and interactive client communication.

Provides asynchronous IO operations and Unix-specific utilities, including support for CGI processing. Offers file system interactions and event-driven network handling through Lwt. Can read and write files, manage processes, and handle HTTP requests in a non-blocking manner. Enables building scalable network applications with Unix-like system integration.
